The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Four persons were injured in three motorcycle accidents in the city since Monday night. A 55-year-old motorcyclist sustained head injuries after the two-wheeler skidded on CR Avenue late on Monday and he fell off. He was taken to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital. Chandi Charan Ghosh, a 55-year-old pedestrian, was injured when a bike hit him on Majherhat bridge on Tuesday afternoon. Motorcyclist John Mathew was also injured. Both were taken to CMRI Hospital. A 12-year-old boy suffered head injuries on Tuesday when a bike hit him in central Calcutta. Kundan Paswan was taken to SSKM Hospital.    Over 50 people demonstrated at SSKM Hospital on Tuesday evening after a baby who underwent a head surgery in the hospital in the morning died. The relatives of the baby complained of anomalies in the death certificate and said nurses had refused to hand over the body to them, said a hospital official. According to hospital authorities, the child, who was admitted to Alex ward died of post-operative complications. The babys family members were asked to submit a written complaint on Wednesday morning, added the official.     Nilima Kahar, a 42-year-old help at a house in Salt Lakes BC block, lodged a police complaint on Tuesday, accusing her employer of beating her up. Nilimas six-year-old daughter was allegedly injured in the ear while trying to protect her mother from the blows. The child is suffering from hearing problems, said Nilima. According to the complaint, the employer attacked Nilima for returning late after buying kerosene.    SFI supporters blocked SP Mukherjee Road, near the Hazra crossing, from 6.45pm to 8.25pm on Tuesday after clashing with Trinamul Chhatra Parishad supporters at Asutosh College. Trinamul members alleged that four of their new members were beaten up by SFI supporters. The Chhatra Parishad members later gheraoed Bhowanipore police station.    Trains were disrupted on the Sealdah-Ranaghat section of Eastern Railways Sealdah division between 1.40pm and 3.40pm on Tuesday after SFI supporters blocked the tracks at Naihati station following a clash with Trinamul Chhatra Parishad supporters at Rishi Bankim Chandra College. Four pairs of EMUs had to be cancelled. The Up Balia Express and the Up Teesta Torsa Express were detained for more than an hour. Two local trains had to be short-terminated and 15 others detained for an hour. The Up Poorvanchal Express had to be diverted via Dankuni. Train services resumed at 3.40pm.     A 27-year-old youth was injured in his right leg after a tanker hit him at Circular Garden Reach Road- Nimak Mahal Road crossing on Tuesday morning. Sardom Shah was taken to SSKM Hospital. The driver of the tanker fled.    About 275 supporters of Pragatishil Indira Congress Chatra Parishad courted arrest by breaking a police cordon at the BB Ganguly Street-Phears Lane crossing on Tuesday afternoon. They were protesting the treatment meted out to the Primary Teachers Training Institutes students and atrocities by SFI supporters.                                                                                                                                                                   
